17 Section 2. Section 46-23-502, MCA, is amended to read:
18 "46-23-502. Definitions. As used in Title 45, chapter 5, part 3 and parts 5 through 7, 46-18-255, and
19 this part, the following definitions apply:
20 (1) "Department" means the department of corrections provided for in 2-15-2301.
21 (2) "Foreign offenses" means a conviction for a sexual offense involving any of the conduct listed
22 in this section that was obtained under the laws of Canada, the United Kingdom, Australia, or New Zealand, or
23 under the laws of any foreign country when the United States department of state, in its country reports on
24 human rights practices, has concluded that an independent judiciary generally or vigorously enforced the right
25 to a fair trial in that country during the year in which the conviction was obtained.
26 (3) "Mental abnormality" means a congenital or acquired condition that affects the mental,
27 emotional, or volitional capacity of a person in a manner that predisposes the person to the commission of one
28 or more sexual offenses to a degree that makes the person a menace to the health and safety of other persons.
